1
00:00:03,545 --> 00:00:08,008
You can survive this.
Make it home. And make it better.

2
00:00:09,051 --> 00:00:10,928
Right my wrongs.

3
00:00:19,061 --> 00:00:21,188
-Dad.
-Survive.

4
00:00:23,022 --> 00:00:24,358
[GUNSHOT]

5
00:00:25,859 --> 00:00:27,861
[OLIVER PANTING]

6
00:00:37,621 --> 00:00:39,248
I hope I didn't hurt you.

7
00:00:41,708 --> 00:00:45,837
At least I can properly thank you now
for saving my life.

8
00:00:46,255 --> 00:00:48,924
If I only knew...

9
00:00:49,132 --> 00:00:52,344
...how you were spending
your nights.

10
00:00:54,137 --> 00:00:56,598
My hope is that I can explain
everything to you...

11
00:00:56,807 --> 00:00:58,809
...to help you understand.

12
00:00:59,017 --> 00:01:00,477
You murdered my father.

13
00:01:01,645 --> 00:01:04,356
You sentenced me to that island...

14
00:01:04,565 --> 00:01:06,817
...to five years of hell.

15
00:01:08,485 --> 00:01:11,530
I'm truly sorry
for what happened to you.

16
00:01:14,116 --> 00:01:16,118
You know I have lost people.

17
00:01:16,326 --> 00:01:18,078
Yeah, your wife.

18
00:01:18,287 --> 00:01:20,205
Do you really think...

19
00:01:20,414 --> 00:01:23,834
...that you're honoring
Tommy's mother...

20
00:01:24,042 --> 00:01:26,670
...by destroying the Glades?

21
00:01:26,878 --> 00:01:28,171
As surely as you believe...

22
00:01:28,380 --> 00:01:30,465
...you're honoring your father
with this hood.

23
00:01:32,676 --> 00:01:36,054
Not a day goes by
I don't miss your father.

24
00:01:37,180 --> 00:01:38,849
You'll see him soon.

25
00:01:44,146 --> 00:01:46,440
You can't beat me, Oliver.

26
00:01:47,024 --> 00:01:49,318
Yes, you're younger
and you're faster.

27
00:01:49,526 --> 00:01:51,945
Yet you always seem
to come up short against me.

28
00:01:53,280 --> 00:01:54,740
Want to know why?

29
00:01:55,657 --> 00:01:58,076
Because you don't know...

30
00:01:58,327 --> 00:02:01,747
...in your heart,
what you're fighting for.

31
00:02:03,123 --> 00:02:06,376
What you're willing to sacrifice,
and I do.

32
00:02:11,089 --> 00:02:12,799
No one can stop
what's about to come.

33
00:02:17,137 --> 00:02:19,514
Not even the vigilante.

34
00:02:34,321 --> 00:02:37,741
Plane's holding steady at 33,000 feet.
The range for missile intercept.

35
00:02:41,036 --> 00:02:42,954
Lock missile one on target.

36
00:02:44,122 --> 00:02:46,083
Missile one locked
on the jet's heat trail.

37
00:02:46,875 --> 00:02:49,044
FRYERS:
Prepare to launch on my mark.

38
00:02:49,252 --> 00:02:51,170
DURAND:
Yes, sir.

39
00:02:57,511 --> 00:02:58,679
[YELLING]

40
00:02:59,346 --> 00:03:00,681
[DURAND GRUNTS]

41
00:03:07,604 --> 00:03:09,940
Fire! Fire the missile now!

42
00:03:29,459 --> 00:03:30,711
[GRUNTS]

43
00:03:46,560 --> 00:03:47,894
[GROANS]

44
00:03:56,069 --> 00:03:57,404
[NECK SNAPS]

45
00:04:07,414 --> 00:04:08,749
[CRACKS]

46
00:04:12,127 --> 00:04:13,462
[GUNSHOT]

47
00:04:16,798 --> 00:04:20,177
I take back every joke about you
sticking a tracking device in your boot.

48
00:04:29,227 --> 00:04:30,729
Felicity's
at Queen Consolidated.

49
00:04:30,937 --> 00:04:33,565
She's going through data
she pulled off Merlyn's network.

50
00:04:33,774 --> 00:04:35,233
-Did she find anything?
-Yeah.

51
00:04:35,442 --> 00:04:37,736
The design schematics
of the earthquake generator.

52
00:04:37,944 --> 00:04:39,112
So we can shut it down.

53
00:04:39,321 --> 00:04:40,781
Assuming we find it in time.

54
00:04:40,947 --> 00:04:41,948
[PHONE RINGS]

55
00:04:43,325 --> 00:04:45,744
DIGGLE: <i>Yeah, Felicity, I got him.</i>
-Thank God.

56
00:04:45,952 --> 00:04:48,079
-Is he okay?
DIGGLE: <i>Mostly.</i>

57
00:04:48,288 --> 00:04:50,957
Okay. I'm on my way.

58
00:04:51,166 --> 00:04:53,376
LANCE:
Miss Smoak.

59
00:04:57,172 --> 00:04:59,299
Where are you off to
in such a hurry?

60
00:05:04,304 --> 00:05:05,972
Please.

61
00:05:08,308 --> 00:05:09,643
Take a seat.

62
00:05:09,851 --> 00:05:11,561
You know, I think I'd rather stand.

63
00:05:14,022 --> 00:05:17,526
-You're not exactly a hardened criminal.
-No, I'm not any kind of criminal.

64
00:05:17,692 --> 00:05:20,570
-What do you call computer hacking?
-A hobby?

65
00:05:21,822 --> 00:05:24,699
That I do not engage in.

66
00:05:24,908 --> 00:05:26,326
Hey, I got a whole mess...

67
00:05:26,535 --> 00:05:29,538
...of gobbledygook I don't understand
but it says otherwise.

68
00:05:30,789 --> 00:05:34,376
I had my tech guy scrub through
your computer at Queen Consolidated.

69
00:05:34,584 --> 00:05:37,087
You used it to hack into
Blackhawk Squad Security...

70
00:05:37,254 --> 00:05:40,090
...research arrows shipped
to a company called Sagittarius...

71
00:05:40,257 --> 00:05:43,342
...and to analyze a water sample
to tie back to a Vertigo drug lab.

72
00:05:43,552 --> 00:05:44,845
These are all cases...

73
00:05:45,053 --> 00:05:47,222
...involving...

74
00:05:47,430 --> 00:05:48,515
...The Hood.

75
00:05:49,182 --> 00:05:50,767
Tell me, Felicity.

76
00:05:51,601 --> 00:05:52,686
What am I thinking?

77
00:05:54,646 --> 00:05:56,022
[PHONE RINGS]

78
00:05:56,189 --> 00:05:58,191
Saved by the bell.

79
00:05:58,525 --> 00:05:59,776
Excuse me.

80
00:06:02,946 --> 00:06:04,948
HOOD: <i>Hello, detective.</i>
-Funny you should call.

81
00:06:05,364 --> 00:06:08,869
-I got your sidekick sitting in front of me.
HOOD: <i>I don't have a sidekick.</i>

82
00:06:09,077 --> 00:06:11,246
When I need help, I call you.

83
00:06:11,454 --> 00:06:14,291
Merlyn plans to level the Glades
with a manmade earthquake...

84
00:06:14,499 --> 00:06:16,626
<i>...using technology
from Unidac Industries.</i>

85
00:06:20,171 --> 00:06:21,548
What?

86
00:06:21,715 --> 00:06:24,467
Ha, ha. Now you're trying
to have fun with me.

87
00:06:24,634 --> 00:06:28,221
I don't know Merlyn's timetable. You need
to evacuate the Glades immediately.

88
00:06:28,387 --> 00:06:30,265
<i>Get as many people
to safety as you can.</i>

89
00:06:30,473 --> 00:06:34,603
Whatever you think of me,
detective, please...

90
00:06:35,270 --> 00:06:36,313
...believe this.

91
00:06:40,191 --> 00:06:42,861
Sounds like you have
bigger problems than me.

92
00:06:48,241 --> 00:06:50,327
Don't leave town.

93
00:06:55,040 --> 00:06:56,541
You know...

94
00:06:57,416 --> 00:07:01,171
...I used to think the vigilante
was a criminal too but it seems to me...

95
00:07:01,379 --> 00:07:05,424
...whoever he is, he's willing to sacrifice
an awful lot to help the people of this city.

96
00:07:08,136 --> 00:07:10,055
Kind of makes him a hero.

97
00:07:10,263 --> 00:07:11,598
Doesn't it?

98
00:07:20,899 --> 00:07:22,817
Look who it is.

99
00:07:23,568 --> 00:07:27,781
-My best friend in life.
-Hey, buddy.

100
00:07:29,699 --> 00:07:31,034
I took your advice, you know.

101
00:07:32,702 --> 00:07:35,914
I went to Laurel's to fight for her.

102
00:07:36,831 --> 00:07:41,294
So imagine my surprise
seeing you there, kissing her.

103
00:07:42,712 --> 00:07:44,881
-I'm sorry.
-No, you're not.

104
00:07:48,510 --> 00:07:51,304
Something's happening
and it involves your father.

105
00:07:51,513 --> 00:07:55,392
-Keep my father out of this.
-Our fathers.

106
00:07:56,309 --> 00:07:58,895
They aren't the men
we thought they were.

107
00:07:59,437 --> 00:08:02,065
They made a plan together...

108
00:08:02,357 --> 00:08:03,984
...to destroy the Glades.

109
00:08:06,361 --> 00:08:09,322
Do you have any idea
what you sound like right now?

110
00:08:09,531 --> 00:08:11,866
Your father's gonna do it.

111
00:08:13,284 --> 00:08:15,870
Because he thinks
it will avenge your mother's death.

112
00:08:16,079 --> 00:08:17,956
Do not talk about my mother.

113
00:08:26,631 --> 00:08:28,717
The difference...

114
00:08:29,217 --> 00:08:31,052
...between us, Tommy...

115
00:08:31,261 --> 00:08:34,723
...is that I didn't find out
the truth about my father...

116
00:08:34,931 --> 00:08:37,225
...until it was too late.

117
00:08:38,309 --> 00:08:39,602
But you've always known...

118
00:08:40,395 --> 00:08:42,272
...deep down...

119
00:08:42,480 --> 00:08:46,860
...you have always known
the man he is.

120
00:08:51,072 --> 00:08:53,533
I wish you would have died
on that island.

121
00:09:18,308 --> 00:09:19,476
Open.

122
00:09:20,393 --> 00:09:21,895
[YELLING]

123
00:09:27,776 --> 00:09:29,277
We need to reprogram
the missile.

124
00:09:29,486 --> 00:09:30,945
I don't know how to reprogram.

125
00:09:33,865 --> 00:09:35,533
-I do.
-Hey, Shado!

126
00:09:39,329 --> 00:09:40,663
[GRUNTS]

127
00:09:50,256 --> 00:09:51,549
Oliver, put the chip in.

128
00:10:41,349 --> 00:10:45,103
Quick, I got a comm stat meeting in five.
I don't want to be late for my funeral.

129
00:10:45,311 --> 00:10:47,480
I've got it under good authority
that Merlyn...

130
00:10:47,689 --> 00:10:50,483
...plans to level the Glades
using an earthquake device...

131
00:10:50,692 --> 00:10:52,193
...made by Unidac Industries.

132
00:10:52,402 --> 00:10:56,364
-Who's your source in all this?
-The vigilante.

133
00:10:58,658 --> 00:10:59,701
He called me.

134
00:11:00,410 --> 00:11:03,037
Yeah, has done
the last few months.

135
00:11:03,580 --> 00:11:05,665
He's been helpful
on some cases.

136
00:11:05,874 --> 00:11:07,792
You asked for the task force
to catch him.

137
00:11:08,001 --> 00:11:11,087
-You swore you'd bring him in.
-I know. I swore to uphold the law.

138
00:11:11,254 --> 00:11:14,257
The law is steady and unchanging.
The law needed to be protected.

139
00:11:15,800 --> 00:11:20,555
But what are laws, rules,
if they don't protect people?

140
00:11:21,472 --> 00:11:24,017
I'm throwing away
my career by telling you this...

141
00:11:24,225 --> 00:11:29,105
...I am willing to sacrifice catching this guy
if it means saving people's lives.

142
00:11:30,273 --> 00:11:31,316
Please.

143
00:11:34,652 --> 00:11:36,362
You're suspended.

144
00:11:37,238 --> 00:11:39,073
Leave your gun and badge
with the duty sergeant.

145
00:11:39,282 --> 00:11:42,660
-Lieutenant...
-Suspension or incarceration.

146
00:11:42,869 --> 00:11:44,537
You choose.

147
00:12:03,264 --> 00:12:04,974
No more lies, Mom.

148
00:12:05,516 --> 00:12:07,268
The Undertaking.

149
00:12:07,685 --> 00:12:08,978
We need to stop it.

150
00:12:09,771 --> 00:12:12,398
Everything I have ever said
or done...

151
00:12:12,607 --> 00:12:15,193
...has been to protect you
and your sister.

152
00:12:16,319 --> 00:12:18,238
What about all those people
in the Glades?

153
00:12:18,446 --> 00:12:19,614
I'm not their mother.

154
00:12:21,449 --> 00:12:24,369
-I spoke to Malcolm.
-You what?

155
00:12:27,413 --> 00:12:28,831
He could have killed you.

156
00:12:31,501 --> 00:12:33,169
He killed your father.

157
00:12:34,921 --> 00:12:36,381
No, he didn't.

158
00:12:37,548 --> 00:12:42,761
After the <i>Gambit</i> went down,
dad and I both made it to the life raft.

159
00:12:43,304 --> 00:12:46,224
And then we drifted, for days.

160
00:12:46,849 --> 00:12:50,937
In the end, there wasn't enough
food and water for both of us.

161
00:12:54,315 --> 00:12:56,401
So he shot himself in the head.

162
00:12:56,609 --> 00:12:58,403
I don't want to hear this.

163
00:12:58,611 --> 00:13:01,447
He sacrificed himself.

164
00:13:01,656 --> 00:13:03,074
So that I could live.

165
00:13:03,283 --> 00:13:05,034
Do you really think...

166
00:13:05,910 --> 00:13:07,495
...that I could go on living...

167
00:13:07,704 --> 00:13:13,001
...knowing that you sacrificed
thousands more in my name?

168
00:13:14,502 --> 00:13:16,879
Mom. Please.

169
00:13:17,796 --> 00:13:21,384
You have to help me
stop Malcolm.

170
00:13:21,592 --> 00:13:24,803
We need to know where the device is.

171
00:13:26,681 --> 00:13:28,683
[PHONE RINGING]

172
00:13:36,815 --> 00:13:38,609
Malcolm.

173
00:13:39,902 --> 00:13:40,945
How can I help you?

174
00:13:44,490 --> 00:13:46,367
I see.

175
00:13:47,410 --> 00:13:50,038
Yes, thank you for calling.

176
00:13:51,039 --> 00:13:54,459
-What is it?
-Malcolm's accelerated his timetable.

177
00:13:54,667 --> 00:13:56,919
The Undertaking is...

178
00:13:58,171 --> 00:13:59,505
...happening tonight.

179
00:14:02,759 --> 00:14:04,469
Where are you going?

180
00:14:09,015 --> 00:14:12,810
Somebody in this family
needs to put an end to this.

181
00:14:15,021 --> 00:14:17,190
Whatever the cost.

182
00:14:29,077 --> 00:14:30,536
LAUREL:
Hi.

183
00:14:35,416 --> 00:14:36,959
Hey.

184
00:14:38,336 --> 00:14:40,004
LAUREL:
I woke up and you were gone.

185
00:14:40,254 --> 00:14:42,965
I'm really sorry about that.

186
00:14:43,341 --> 00:14:47,011
Oliver, I'm trying not to think
that our history's repeating.

187
00:14:47,261 --> 00:14:50,181
-That you're scared again.
-No.

188
00:14:51,891 --> 00:14:52,934
That's not it.

189
00:14:53,935 --> 00:14:56,604
Then will you tell me
what's going on with you?

190
00:15:01,359 --> 00:15:03,861
There are so many things...

191
00:15:04,070 --> 00:15:06,614
...that I have wanted to tell you...

192
00:15:06,823 --> 00:15:08,324
...for so long.

193
00:15:11,786 --> 00:15:14,163
I never told you what happened to me
on the island.

194
00:15:14,831 --> 00:15:16,833
You didn't have to.

195
00:15:17,083 --> 00:15:19,127
I can see that it changed you.

196
00:15:19,627 --> 00:15:22,964
That's the thing.
Laurel, it didn't.

197
00:15:23,881 --> 00:15:26,843
Those five years didn't change me.
They just...

198
00:15:27,301 --> 00:15:32,390
...they scraped away
all the things that I wasn't...

199
00:15:32,598 --> 00:15:36,602
...and revealed the person
I always was, which is the person...

200
00:15:39,188 --> 00:15:40,857
That's who you always saw.

201
00:15:42,608 --> 00:15:45,820
I don't know how you saw it,
but you did.

202
00:15:46,028 --> 00:15:50,158
Nobody in my life
is who I thought they were.

203
00:15:50,408 --> 00:15:51,659
Except you.

204
00:16:07,550 --> 00:16:10,178
Laurel, I need you
to do something for me.

205
00:16:10,386 --> 00:16:13,347
-Stay out of the Glades tonight.
-Why?

206
00:16:14,140 --> 00:16:16,142
You'll know soon.

207
00:16:17,101 --> 00:16:18,478
One way or the other.

208
00:16:20,521 --> 00:16:22,106
I have to go.

209
00:16:33,743 --> 00:16:35,119
It's over.

210
00:16:35,369 --> 00:16:37,705
Laurel and me, I mean.

211
00:16:37,914 --> 00:16:41,167
She's with Oliver, again.
Always.

212
00:16:41,375 --> 00:16:42,627
I'm sorry, son.

213
00:16:42,877 --> 00:16:47,423
Yeah, and he said you wanted to nuke
the Glades or something.

214
00:16:49,509 --> 00:16:52,136
It's funny, Scotch doesn't make it
any more believable.

215
00:16:53,012 --> 00:16:56,682
Maybe after your jihad,
we can, uh, grab some steaks.

216
00:17:00,686 --> 00:17:01,896
It's true, Tommy.

217
00:17:03,064 --> 00:17:05,316
It's the reason
I closed your mother's clinic.

218
00:17:05,983 --> 00:17:07,443
I didn't wanna see it leveled.

219
00:17:10,530 --> 00:17:11,781
What?

220
00:17:11,989 --> 00:17:14,742
I have something
I'd like you to listen to.

221
00:17:18,246 --> 00:17:20,540
The night your mother died...

222
00:17:22,416 --> 00:17:23,417
...she called me.

223
00:17:25,294 --> 00:17:26,796
I awoke to a voicemail from her.

224
00:17:27,213 --> 00:17:32,009
-Dad.
-Her final gift to me.

225
00:17:33,344 --> 00:17:36,681
REBECCA [ON RECORDING]:
<i>Malcolm, I'm in trouble.</i>

226
00:17:36,931 --> 00:17:39,433
<i>I told, I told him
to take everything.</i>

227
00:17:39,600 --> 00:17:41,435
<i>My money...</i>

228
00:17:41,936 --> 00:17:43,729
<i>...my ring.</i>

229
00:17:44,146 --> 00:17:45,439
Turn it off.

230
00:17:45,606 --> 00:17:46,857
REBECCA:
<i>They shot me.</i>

231
00:17:47,066 --> 00:17:48,985
<i>I screamed for help...</i>

232
00:17:49,193 --> 00:17:51,529
-<i>...but no one would come. God.</i>
-No one would come.

233
00:17:51,737 --> 00:17:55,700
REBECCA:
<i>Malcolm, I don't want to die alone.</i>

234
00:17:57,577 --> 00:18:02,456
She bled out into the pavement
while people passed and did nothing.

235
00:18:05,042 --> 00:18:08,963
Your mother built her clinic in the Glades
because she wanted to save this city.

236
00:18:10,089 --> 00:18:12,216
It can't be saved.

237
00:18:12,883 --> 00:18:16,971
Because the people there
don't want it to be saved.

238
00:18:17,638 --> 00:18:19,640
-So you kill them all...?
-Yes!

239
00:18:19,849 --> 00:18:22,685
They deserve to die!
All of them!

240
00:18:22,893 --> 00:18:25,271
The way she died!

241
00:18:32,486 --> 00:18:34,363
The Undertaking
is happening tonight.

242
00:18:37,408 --> 00:18:39,076
Felicity may have found something.

243
00:18:40,745 --> 00:18:43,414
This symbol is the map
of the old subway tunnel system.

244
00:18:43,623 --> 00:18:46,667
That's got us thinking the Undertaking
is connected to the Glades.

245
00:18:46,876 --> 00:18:49,128
-What if it's more specific?
-What do you mean?

246
00:18:49,337 --> 00:18:52,256
If I had a machine that could trigger
an earthquake...

247
00:18:52,506 --> 00:18:55,843
...in an otherwise geologically stable area,
where would I position it?

248
00:18:57,428 --> 00:18:59,639
-Underground.
-Yeah.

249
00:19:01,182 --> 00:19:02,850
This is a U.S. geological survey...

250
00:19:03,059 --> 00:19:05,770
...of the tectonic plates
running underneath Starling City.

251
00:19:06,020 --> 00:19:09,523
This red line here is a known fault
that runs right below the Glades.

252
00:19:09,690 --> 00:19:12,360
About a mile. Fault runs under
the old 10th Street subway.

253
00:19:12,652 --> 00:19:15,780
Dollars to doughnuts, the seismic device
is somewhere along there.

254
00:19:16,030 --> 00:19:17,531
I know where it is.

255
00:19:19,200 --> 00:19:21,202
[PHONE VIBRATES]

256
00:19:23,537 --> 00:19:24,830
Now is not a good time.

257
00:19:25,039 --> 00:19:26,457
Yeah, understate much?

258
00:19:26,666 --> 00:19:29,418
Mom has a whole bunch
of reporters here.

259
00:19:29,627 --> 00:19:33,422
She's holding a press conference
or something.

260
00:19:34,048 --> 00:19:35,299
What channel?

261
00:19:35,716 --> 00:19:37,051
It looks like all of them.

262
00:19:37,635 --> 00:19:40,554
Felicity, pull up the local news,
please.

263
00:19:42,556 --> 00:19:44,183
<i>My name is Moira Dearden Queen.</i>

264
00:19:44,392 --> 00:19:48,479
<i>I am the acting CEO
of Queen Consolidated.</i>

265
00:19:48,688 --> 00:19:51,774
And God forgive me,
I have failed this city.

266
00:19:52,900 --> 00:19:56,237
For the past five years,
under the threat for my life...

267
00:19:56,445 --> 00:19:58,864
...and the lives of my family...

268
00:20:00,157 --> 00:20:01,617
...I have been complicit...

269
00:20:01,826 --> 00:20:05,454
...in an undertaking
with one horrible purpose.

270
00:20:09,083 --> 00:20:11,669
To destroy the Glades
and everyone in it.

271
00:20:13,504 --> 00:20:15,589
I realize now
that my family's safety...

272
00:20:15,756 --> 00:20:19,677
...will mean nothing
if I let this dreadful act occur.

273
00:20:20,094 --> 00:20:21,637
But you need to know...

274
00:20:22,138 --> 00:20:26,183
<i>...that the architect
of this nightmare...</i>

275
00:20:27,685 --> 00:20:29,019
<i>...is Malcolm Merlyn.</i>

276
00:20:29,895 --> 00:20:30,938
[SCREAMS]

277
00:20:31,397 --> 00:20:34,024
Yes, and I have proof
that he has killed dozens...

278
00:20:34,233 --> 00:20:36,193
...in pursuit of this madness.

279
00:20:36,402 --> 00:20:38,904
Adam Hunt, Frank Chen...

280
00:20:39,113 --> 00:20:40,781
...and my husband...

281
00:20:42,116 --> 00:20:43,784
...Robert.

282
00:20:49,290 --> 00:20:50,332
<i>Please.</i>

283
00:20:50,958 --> 00:20:53,878
<i>If you reside in the Glades,
you need to get out now.</i>

284
00:20:54,628 --> 00:20:57,882
<i>Your lives and the lives
of your children depend on it.</i>

285
00:20:58,966 --> 00:21:00,509
Please.

286
00:21:03,721 --> 00:21:05,723
[REPORTERS YELLING INDISTINCTLY]

287
00:21:07,933 --> 00:21:11,520
-I don't understand.
-I'm sorry. I love you.

288
00:21:11,729 --> 00:21:13,731
-I love Roy.
-Roy?

289
00:21:13,939 --> 00:21:16,442
He lives in the Glades.

290
00:21:16,901 --> 00:21:19,278
-I can't leave him there.
-Sweetheart. Thea.

291
00:21:19,487 --> 00:21:21,614
HILTON: You're under arrest
for conspiracy to murder.

292
00:21:21,781 --> 00:21:24,450
Anything you say can and will be used
against you in a court of law.

293
00:21:24,617 --> 00:21:26,035
You have the right to an attorney.

294
00:21:26,202 --> 00:21:28,245
TOMMY:
Is it true?

295
00:21:28,996 --> 00:21:31,040
Did you kill all those people?

296
00:21:32,917 --> 00:21:34,585
I did what I had to do.

297
00:22:01,737 --> 00:22:03,197
OFFICER:
Freeze!

298
00:22:03,489 --> 00:22:05,699
Malcolm Merlyn, you are under arrest.

299
00:22:07,493 --> 00:22:08,536
Don't move.

300
00:22:12,414 --> 00:22:13,582
Dad, no.

301
00:22:18,546 --> 00:22:20,130
Please, Dad.

302
00:22:22,091 --> 00:22:23,592
Stay back.

303
00:22:23,926 --> 00:22:25,219
I don't want to hurt you.

304
00:22:25,511 --> 00:22:27,304
You can't.

305
00:22:27,763 --> 00:22:29,640
And you can't stop me.

306
00:22:33,727 --> 00:22:35,312
FELICITY:
Oliver, I'm sorry.

307
00:22:37,147 --> 00:22:38,941
Don't be.

308
00:22:39,233 --> 00:22:42,152
She gave those people a chance.

309
00:22:42,611 --> 00:22:44,362
I thought Merlyn broke your bow.

310
00:22:48,409 --> 00:22:50,327
I have another.

311
00:22:53,664 --> 00:22:55,541
I was going over
the device schematics.

312
00:22:55,749 --> 00:22:57,918
The device can be set
for a timed detonation...

313
00:22:58,085 --> 00:23:01,964
-...or remote activated by mobile transmitter.
-Something Merlyn could have on him.

314
00:23:02,172 --> 00:23:04,550
If we can just get our hands
on this transmitter...

315
00:23:04,758 --> 00:23:08,012
-...we don't need to track down the device.
-It's too big an if.

316
00:23:08,262 --> 00:23:09,555
I need you in the subway.

317
00:23:09,763 --> 00:23:13,517
-Find the device, disarm it.
-So you can take on Merlyn by yourself?

318
00:23:15,269 --> 00:23:17,771
-I have to.
-Oh, he'll kill you, Oliver.

319
00:23:20,524 --> 00:23:21,650
I know.

320
00:23:24,695 --> 00:23:27,323
He's beaten me twice.

321
00:23:28,157 --> 00:23:30,117
And I don't know how to stop him.

322
00:23:32,328 --> 00:23:35,080
Okay. How about this time,
you bring along something...

323
00:23:35,247 --> 00:23:37,458
...you didn't have
the last time you two fought.

324
00:23:38,167 --> 00:23:39,627
-Me.
-I can't let you.

325
00:23:39,835 --> 00:23:41,795
I can't let you do this
by yourself, man.

326
00:23:42,796 --> 00:23:46,133
Oliver, you are not alone, not since
you brought me into this.

327
00:23:47,927 --> 00:23:49,178
Us into this.

328
00:23:52,389 --> 00:23:53,807
Besides, Army regulations.

329
00:23:54,224 --> 00:23:56,644
A soldier never lets a brother
go into battle alone.

330
00:24:03,817 --> 00:24:06,028
-I'm out of bows.
-I got my gun.

331
00:24:06,236 --> 00:24:08,822
I guess it's up to me
to do the dismantling.

332
00:24:09,031 --> 00:24:10,532
This whole area is ground zero.

333
00:24:10,741 --> 00:24:12,201
I want you out of here.

334
00:24:12,409 --> 00:24:14,703
If you're not leaving,
I'm not leaving.

335
00:24:15,204 --> 00:24:17,748
Besides, if I don't deactivate
the device, who will?

336
00:24:27,549 --> 00:24:29,426
[PHONE RINGS]

337
00:24:29,593 --> 00:24:30,636
You were right.

338
00:24:30,844 --> 00:24:32,346
I need one more thing from you.

339
00:24:32,554 --> 00:24:36,642
-Yeah? What do I got left to give?
-I know where Merlyn is keeping the device.

340
00:24:37,351 --> 00:24:40,646
It's in an abandoned subway station
near Pap Street.

341
00:24:40,854 --> 00:24:44,984
LANCE: <i>How do you know?</i>
-That's where his wife was murdered.

342
00:24:45,192 --> 00:24:48,362
[OVER PHONE] <i>I need someone I can trust
to deactivate the device.</i>

343
00:24:50,948 --> 00:24:54,702
We have a mutual friend that I think
could talk you through it.

344
00:24:55,202 --> 00:24:57,705
She says you care
about the people of this city...

345
00:24:57,913 --> 00:24:59,540
...that it needs you.

346
00:25:00,290 --> 00:25:02,584
Right now, detective...

347
00:25:03,794 --> 00:25:05,254
...it needs you.

348
00:25:11,301 --> 00:25:13,303
[YELLING]

349
00:25:17,808 --> 00:25:20,936
REPORTER [ON TV]: <i>Earlier today,
Moira Queen, CEO of Queen Consolidated...</i>

350
00:25:21,145 --> 00:25:24,064
<i>...admitted to a conspiracy
to destroy the Glades.</i>

351
00:25:24,273 --> 00:25:27,401
<i>Everyone within a five-mile radius
has been asked to evacuate.</i>

352
00:25:27,901 --> 00:25:28,902
MAN [OVER PA]:
<i>Stay calm.</i>

353
00:25:29,111 --> 00:25:32,573
<i>Do not rush and do not panic.</i>

354
00:25:55,721 --> 00:25:59,058
<i>Proceed out of the Glades
in an orderly manner.</i>

355
00:26:04,605 --> 00:26:05,939
[GRUNTING]

356
00:26:22,623 --> 00:26:24,666
Looks like we missed him.

357
00:26:31,465 --> 00:26:32,758
Shado.

358
00:26:33,842 --> 00:26:35,593
Slade.

359
00:26:55,239 --> 00:26:57,157
[SLADE LAUGHING]

360
00:26:58,659 --> 00:27:00,994
Oh, I should have figured.

361
00:27:01,662 --> 00:27:04,164
You couldn't save the day...

362
00:27:04,790 --> 00:27:08,127
-...without making a mess.
-Where's Shado?

363
00:27:08,794 --> 00:27:11,004
-I thought she was with you.
FRYERS: Actually...

364
00:27:12,589 --> 00:27:13,841
...she's with me.

365
00:27:14,341 --> 00:27:16,760
Let her go. It's over, Fyers.

366
00:27:22,808 --> 00:27:24,268
Let her go.

367
00:27:24,935 --> 00:27:26,311
Amazing.

368
00:27:26,520 --> 00:27:28,814
A two-year operation undone...

369
00:27:29,022 --> 00:27:32,526
...because a young playboy
happened to wash up on the shore...

370
00:27:32,693 --> 00:27:35,863
...and now here you are, a killer.

371
00:27:37,322 --> 00:27:40,534
You wanted nothing more
than to leave this island...

372
00:27:40,742 --> 00:27:42,035
...and now you can.

373
00:27:42,244 --> 00:27:45,706
I can call in a rescue ship,
you can go home.

374
00:27:45,914 --> 00:27:47,791
Tell me, Mr. Queen.

375
00:27:48,041 --> 00:27:51,795
Are you prepared to sacrifice
your freedom for her?

376
00:28:06,351 --> 00:28:07,978
Guess so.

377
00:28:20,782 --> 00:28:22,075
[COUGHING NEARBY]

378
00:28:23,493 --> 00:28:25,078
Tommy.

379
00:28:25,579 --> 00:28:28,790
-Tommy.
-Oliver.

380
00:28:30,292 --> 00:28:31,585
Where's your father?

381
00:28:32,794 --> 00:28:33,837
I don't know.

382
00:28:35,297 --> 00:28:36,340
You were right.

383
00:28:37,299 --> 00:28:40,844
-You were right about him.
DIGGLE: Oliver.

384
00:28:45,140 --> 00:28:46,308
Are you gonna kill him?

385
00:28:50,979 --> 00:28:52,981
Get to safety.

386
00:29:01,531 --> 00:29:03,533
Looks like a false wall.

387
00:29:14,711 --> 00:29:15,796
Welcome, gentlemen.

388
00:29:16,004 --> 00:29:17,547
I've been waiting for you.

389
00:29:17,756 --> 00:29:20,217
I wanted to see you
watch your city die.

390
00:29:20,425 --> 00:29:23,720
-Where's the transmitter?
-Somewhere I can easily get to it.

391
00:29:23,929 --> 00:29:26,348
I doubt it. You'll be too dead.

392
00:29:45,409 --> 00:29:46,952
[GROANS]

393
00:29:51,331 --> 00:29:54,209
Stairs, Oliver. Go, go.

394
00:29:59,506 --> 00:30:02,884
So tell me, are you ready to die?

395
00:30:05,304 --> 00:30:08,432
FELICITY: <i>You found it yet, detective?</i>
-I'm not sure what I'm looking for.

396
00:30:08,682 --> 00:30:09,933
You want me to describe it?

397
00:30:12,019 --> 00:30:14,062
No, I got it.

398
00:30:17,649 --> 00:30:21,069
FELICITY: <i>You should see something that
looks like a circuit board. Pull it out.</i>

399
00:30:22,321 --> 00:30:24,614
<i>Do you see a timer?</i>

400
00:30:26,199 --> 00:30:27,409
Seven minutes.

401
00:30:27,617 --> 00:30:30,245
Okay. Well, the good news is...

402
00:30:30,454 --> 00:30:33,040
...this is going to be
a paperweight in three.

403
00:30:33,248 --> 00:30:35,959
MAN [OVER PA]:
<i>Everyone leave the Glades. I repeat...</i>

404
00:30:36,752 --> 00:30:38,378
<i>...leave the Glades now.</i>

405
00:30:38,587 --> 00:30:40,339
MAN 1: What do you got there, grandpa?
-Hey.

406
00:30:40,505 --> 00:30:43,008
MAN 2: Please, please, it's all I have.
ROY: Hey.

407
00:30:45,135 --> 00:30:47,387
Hey. Back off.

408
00:30:47,596 --> 00:30:49,931
Learn how to count, jerkwad.
There's three of us.

409
00:30:50,140 --> 00:30:51,433
Oh, is that right?

410
00:31:01,318 --> 00:31:03,487
-Because I only count one.
-With a gun.

411
00:31:09,076 --> 00:31:11,870
-Where did you learn how to do that?
-I have wicked aim.

412
00:31:13,455 --> 00:31:14,581
I went to your house.

413
00:31:14,790 --> 00:31:17,584
I figured I'd run for my life
with everyone else. Did you...?

414
00:31:17,751 --> 00:31:19,711
-Did you come to rescue me?
-Yeah.

415
00:31:21,129 --> 00:31:22,672
Come on.

416
00:31:40,899 --> 00:31:41,900
[ARROW BEEPS]

417
00:31:44,403 --> 00:31:47,072
Look for three wires,
you need a green one...

418
00:31:47,906 --> 00:31:49,699
...a yellow and one blue.

419
00:31:49,908 --> 00:31:52,577
-<i>Cut the blue one.</i>
-All right, I got it, I got it.

420
00:31:53,495 --> 00:31:54,996
[WHIRRING]

421
00:31:59,709 --> 00:32:01,628
Oh, my God.

422
00:32:05,298 --> 00:32:08,009
LANCE: <i>No, no, no.</i>
-There must be an anti-tamper safeguard.

423
00:32:08,218 --> 00:32:10,470
<i>Hold on. I'm gonna figure out
how to override it.</i>

424
00:32:12,264 --> 00:32:14,182
Not enough time.
There's not enough time.

425
00:32:14,391 --> 00:32:16,935
-Just hold on.
LANCE: <i>Not enough time.</i>

426
00:32:20,272 --> 00:32:22,357
-<i>Laurel.</i>
-Dad.

427
00:32:22,566 --> 00:32:26,361
Don't worry, I got your message
and I did not come into work today.

428
00:32:26,570 --> 00:32:28,613
Save it, kiddo,
we both know you're there.

429
00:32:28,822 --> 00:32:33,034
<i>You got to get out of the Glades
right now. Okay, please.</i>

430
00:32:34,077 --> 00:32:36,329
-Dad?
LANCE: <i>Right now, Laurel.</i>

431
00:32:36,538 --> 00:32:37,831
Right now, Laurel.

432
00:32:38,165 --> 00:32:39,958
Daddy, you're scaring me.

433
00:32:40,917 --> 00:32:42,878
Sorry, but I'm not...

434
00:32:44,129 --> 00:32:45,338
I'm not gonna make it.

435
00:32:45,839 --> 00:32:47,424
What?

436
00:32:48,175 --> 00:32:50,677
-What?
LANCE: <i>You have to promise me one thing.</i>

437
00:32:52,304 --> 00:32:53,763
You're not gonna die with me.

438
00:32:54,598 --> 00:32:57,017
[OVER PHONE]
<i>You have to go on with your life.</i>

439
00:32:57,225 --> 00:33:00,395
After your sister died, I pushed people away,
I became like a ghost.

440
00:33:00,604 --> 00:33:03,231
Didn't think I had the right to live
if my baby couldn't.

441
00:33:05,442 --> 00:33:08,487
<i>Promise me you're not gonna make
the same mistakes as I did.</i>

442
00:33:10,655 --> 00:33:13,158
Promise me, Laurel.

443
00:33:13,366 --> 00:33:15,118
[OVER PHONE]
<i>Promise me.</i>

444
00:33:16,786 --> 00:33:18,788
I promise.

445
00:33:27,130 --> 00:33:28,798
I love you, honey, now and forever.

446
00:33:29,633 --> 00:33:31,259
I love you.

447
00:33:33,303 --> 00:33:34,930
Dad.

448
00:33:37,140 --> 00:33:41,645
Detective Lance? I need
you to listen to me very carefully.

449
00:33:43,772 --> 00:33:46,525
You do know how dangerous it is
to text and drive, right?

450
00:33:46,733 --> 00:33:48,026
-It can wait.
-It can't.

451
00:33:48,193 --> 00:33:52,155
-I'm trying to find another route out of here.
-Let me. It's not worth the risk.

452
00:33:53,156 --> 00:33:54,449
Roy.

453
00:33:56,743 --> 00:33:57,869
Roy.

454
00:33:58,078 --> 00:34:00,413
Help me out.
Help me out. Help me out.

455
00:34:00,622 --> 00:34:02,874
Roy, stop.

456
00:34:03,083 --> 00:34:05,627
The device is about to go off
any second.

457
00:34:08,380 --> 00:34:12,467
-I can't leave any of them behind.
-I know you have something to prove.

458
00:34:12,676 --> 00:34:15,303
But you're not the vigilante.

459
00:34:15,512 --> 00:34:18,473
Look, I can't do this
unless I know you're safe.

460
00:34:19,391 --> 00:34:21,768
Then you better haul ass
out of here too.

461
00:35:01,600 --> 00:35:04,352
Don't struggle. It's over.

462
00:35:05,145 --> 00:35:07,272
There was never any doubt
in the outcome.

463
00:35:07,480 --> 00:35:11,484
Don't worry. Your mother and sister
will be joining you in death.

464
00:35:11,693 --> 00:35:13,153
ROBERT:
Survive.

465
00:35:20,785 --> 00:35:22,579
[MALCOLM GRUNTS]

466
00:35:29,836 --> 00:35:34,799
Thank you for teaching me
what I'm fighting for.

467
00:35:37,927 --> 00:35:39,512
But my father taught me how.

468
00:35:50,065 --> 00:35:51,608
Come on.

469
00:35:53,652 --> 00:35:54,903
[POWERS DOWN]

470
00:36:01,576 --> 00:36:03,703
FELICITY:
<i>Oliver, Lance did it.</i>

471
00:36:04,954 --> 00:36:06,665
It's over.

472
00:36:07,040 --> 00:36:11,670
If I've learned anything
as a successful businessman, it's...

473
00:36:11,836 --> 00:36:12,879
[COUGHS]

474
00:36:13,046 --> 00:36:15,382
...redundancy.

475
00:36:15,548 --> 00:36:17,008
[GROANS]

476
00:36:26,518 --> 00:36:28,311
Felicity...

477
00:36:28,895 --> 00:36:32,107
<i>...there's another device.
There's two of them.</i>

478
00:36:41,324 --> 00:36:42,951
LANCE:
What the hell's happening?

479
00:36:46,996 --> 00:36:48,623
Okay, that's enough.

480
00:37:11,479 --> 00:37:13,231
I turned the damn thing off.

481
00:37:13,982 --> 00:37:16,651
Merlyn had a second device.

482
00:37:17,694 --> 00:37:20,697
Laurel. She's at CNRI.

483
00:37:21,906 --> 00:37:24,367
Go. Go!

484
00:37:43,762 --> 00:37:45,680
Laurel.

485
00:37:46,556 --> 00:37:49,851
-Oliver?
-Are you okay?

486
00:37:51,394 --> 00:37:53,021
Yeah.

487
00:37:54,272 --> 00:37:55,607
[SOBS]

488
00:37:57,442 --> 00:38:00,695
The damage seems to be contained
on the east side...

489
00:38:01,362 --> 00:38:04,574
-<i>...past Wells Street.</i>
-Laurel.

490
00:38:05,909 --> 00:38:09,329
-Are you gonna be okay?
-Go, Oliver. Go, go, go.

491
00:38:13,082 --> 00:38:15,460
Help. Please.

492
00:38:22,091 --> 00:38:24,719
Please! Help me!

493
00:38:26,763 --> 00:38:27,889
Tommy.

494
00:38:28,389 --> 00:38:29,641
What are you doing here?

495
00:38:29,849 --> 00:38:32,852
I kind of figured
that you might come back to CNRI.

496
00:38:33,061 --> 00:38:34,813
[TOMMY GRUNTING]

497
00:38:34,979 --> 00:38:37,065
You came here for me?

498
00:38:40,652 --> 00:38:42,362
I love you.

